  "body": "When running and stopping lodestar quickly the ENR file is empty and while loading this happens\r\n```\r\n  âœ– SyntaxError: Unexpected end of JSON input\r\nlodestar_1    |     at JSON.parse (<anonymous>)\r\nlodestar_1    |     at parse (/usr/app/packages/lodestar-cli/src/util/file.ts:35:19)\r\nlodestar_1    |     at readFile (/usr/app/packages/lodestar-cli/src/util/file.ts:76:10)\r\nlodestar_1    |     at readEnr (/usr/app/packages/lodestar-cli/src/network/enr.ts:17:24)\r\nlodestar_1    |     at Object.beaconHandler [as handler] (/usr/app/packages/lodestar-cli/src/cmds/beacon/handler.ts:32:15)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe ENR loader should validate it better and create a new one if corrupt or empty instead of stalling the entire process",
